        description: "La Teste-de-Buch, the historic municipality of the Arcachon Bay encompassing the Dune du Pilat and Pyla-sur-Mer, is connected to Bordeaux in 40 min via the A660 and A63.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A660 from La Teste-de-Buch then the A63 towards Bordeaux, crossing the Landes forest and the Pessac-Léognan vineyards.",
        introduction: "La Teste-de-Buch is the largest municipality in the Arcachon Bay area, encompassing the famous Dune du Pilat, the upscale Pyla-sur-Mer seaside quarter, the ancient Usagere forest (a communal forest managed under customary rights dating back to the Middle Ages) and Lake Cazaux, France's second-largest natural lake. This municipality of over 27,000 inhabitants is the economic hub of the southern Bay, with its La Teste oyster port, its lively covered market and its commercial zone serving the entire Arcachon Bay. The journey to Bordeaux first crosses the majestic maritime pine forest of the Landes de Gascogne, planted under Napoleon III to drain the Landes marshes, then the vineyards of the Pessac-Leognan appellation, one of the most prestigious on Bordeaux's left bank. Chateau Haut-Brion, the only Premier Cru Classe located within the Bordeaux conurbation, lies on this route. This trip is used daily by Bay residents working in Bordeaux, tourists combining beach stays with city visits, and travellers connecting at Bordeaux Saint-Jean station.",
